Snakes copulate by twining around one another; and they have no testicles and no penis, as I have already observed - no penis because they have no legs, no testicles ... because of their length. For because they are naturally elongated, if there were further delay in the region of the testicles, the semen would grow cool because of its slow passage. (This happens in the case of men who have large penises; they are less fertile than those with moderate penises because cold semen is not fertile and semen that is carried a long way cools.)</q></blockquote>
